msgid "Frame Defaults"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:18-1
msgid ""
"When you create a frame, several default settings are used for Validation "
"Rules and Frame Events. It is helpful to be aware of these defaults if you "
"need to change the rules under which a frame is active, or if you need to "
"change the functionality of a frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:19-1
msgid "Default Frame Events"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:20-1
msgid ""
"When a frame is created, one frame event is always assigned, On Frame Key, "
"set to speak the contents of the frame. This frame event is added even if "
"you do not assign a keystroke to the frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:21-1
msgid ""
"The other frame events that are assigned depend on the options selected "
"during creation of the frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:22-1
msgid ""
"The fifth page of the frame creation dialogs prompts you to specify how your "
"frame will echo text newly displayed within the frame. The choice you select "
"determines the other frame event that is added."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:24-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Silent</b>: An On Text frame event is added "
"with the action set to Suppress Script Event. This prevents the JAWS "
"scripting New Text Event from causing text to be spoken."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:25-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">Highlight</b>: An On Text frame event is "
"added set to filter for highlighted text only, with the action set to Speak "
"Text Filter. This frame event speaks the text that caused the frame event to "
"take place, in this case, the highlighted text."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:26-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">All</b>: An On Text frame event is added "
"that does not filter for any specific sort of text, and with the action set "
"to Speak Text Filter. In this case, all text within the frame is spoken any "
"time new text is displayed within the frame."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:27-1
msgid ""
"<b style=\"font-weight: bold;\">JAWS Screen Echo</b>: No frame event is "
"added when this choice is selected, and the way JAWS echoes text newly "
"displayed in the frame is determined by default JAWS screen echo settings."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:29-1
msgid ""
"For more information, please refer to <a href=\"events.htm\">Frame Events</"
"a>."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.h2:30-1
msgid "Default Validation Rules"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:31-1
msgid "When a frame is created, two default Validation Rules are added:"
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:33-1
msgid ""
"A rule is added based on the Window Title in the application. When you later "
"use this frame, it is active if the window title in the application contains "
"the same text as was present in the window title when the frame was created. "
"If you create a frame in an application in which the name of the open "
"document is reflected in the title bar, you will need to modify this rule or "
"your frame will only be active when that document is open."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.ul.li:34-1
msgid ""
"A rule is added based on the window class in the application window or "
"control. When you later use this frame, it is active if the window class in "
"the application window or control contains the same information as was "
"present when the frame was created."
msgstr ""

#: HTM_po_nelkul%5CFrame_Defaults.htm%2Bhtml.body.p:36-1
msgid ""
"For more information, please refer to <a href=\"rules.htm\">Validation "
"Rules</a>."
msgstr ""

